<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
Most of the coffee crops were located near secondary forest patches with some individuals of trees as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Cedrela" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cedrela odorata" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="odorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Cedrela odorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
