<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
In May 2015, a specimen of another species, 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epidendrum laxicaule" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxicaule">Epidendrum aff. laxicaule</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., was found growing as an epiphyte in a montane forest in the western part of Amazonas department in northern Peru, in the Cajaruro district of Utcubamba province, at an elevation of 1685 m. It was observed and validated with photographs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Other undescribed species of the Laxicaule Group found in Amazonas A, B, C Epidendrum aff. laxicaule sp. nov. and E. Epidendrum lufinorum D, E Epidendrum aff. megalopentadactylum sp. nov. Photographs by L. Pillaca (A, B, C) and L. Ocupa (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.184.70844.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/605551" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">5A, B, C</figureCitation>
) by Luis Pillaca and shows vegetative and morphological characteristics similar to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. laxicaule" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxicaule">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E. laxicaule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. lufinorum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lufinorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E. lufinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it has flat and thick, narrow leaves, a much more prominent vesicle at the apex of the ovary and the narrower lip with three parallel and central ribs. Pillaca indicates that the area where the specimen was found has been destroyed due to agricultural encroachment.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.184.70844.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/605551" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Other undescribed species of the 
<taxonomicName genus="Laxicaule" lsidName="Laxicaule" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" rank="genus">Laxicaule</taxonomicName>
