A year later, in the same department, but in the province of Bagua, district of Aramango, a specimen of an additional species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hagsater &amp; Huayta" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epidendrum megalopentadactylum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="megalopentadactylum">Epidendrum aff. megalopentadactylum</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., was found as part of the private collection of Ricardo Saens Saavedra†. This specimen observed and photographed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Other undescribed species of the Laxicaule Group found in Amazonas A, B, C Epidendrum aff. laxicaule sp. nov. and E. Epidendrum lufinorum D, E Epidendrum aff. megalopentadactylum sp. nov. Photographs by L. Pillaca (A, B, C) and L. Ocupa (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.184.70844.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/605551" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">5 D, E</figureCitation>
) by Luis Ocupa, presents morphological characteristics similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. megalopentadactylum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="megalopentadactylum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="55">E. megalopentadactylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as pendulous plants with flat leaves, conduplicate at the base, strongly laterally compressed and ancipitous stems and an entire lip, but is distinguished by the presence of a vesicle and the lip without ribs.
